---
By: Arthur Schopenhauer
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 421
    Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Self
---
A man is best off if he is thrown upon his own resources, and can be all in
all to himself, and Cicero goes so far as to say that a man who is in this
condition cannot fail to be happy.
